snippet.title: Paul Mescal And Andrew Scott Talk Dublin, Simone Rocha And More | ELLE UK
snippet.description:
Great double acts in Hollywood are scarcely hard to come by. But, this year, few have felt more natural, or charismatic, than the coming together of Irish heartthrobs Paul Mescal and Andrew Scott. So, when in the middle of promotion of their film All of Us Strangers, we had to catch this very natural craic for ourselves.

Above, the actor’s play a game of ‘Ask Me Anything.’

#PaulMescal #AndrewScott #AskMeAnything

snippet.title: Andrew Scott and Paul Mescal on creating intimacy in All of Us Strangers | BAFTA Interview
snippet.description:
Andrew Scott (Adam), Paul Mescal (Harry), Jamie Bell (Dad) and director & writer Andrew Haigh sat down with BAFTA to discuss their mysterious and romantic film, All Of Us Strangers. They discuss the on-screen chemistry between Andrew and Paul; the complexities of playing a parent; and which scene was their favourite to film.

snippet.title: ALL OF US STRANGERS | Behind-The-Scenes Broadcast Special | Searchlight Pictures
snippet.description:
Discover the beauty and mystery of All of Us Strangers in this half-hour broadcast special, originally airing on ABC. Cast and filmmakers take us behind-the-scenes, as they explore love’s multifaceted dimensions and unspoken dialogs we wish we could share with our loved ones.
 

From director Andrew Haigh. One night in his near-empty tower block in contemporary London, Adam (Andrew Scott) has a chance encounter with a mysterious neighbor Harry (Paul Mescal), which punctures the rhythm of his everyday life. As a relationship develops between them, Adam is preoccupied with memories of the past and finds himself drawn back to the suburban town where he grew up, and the childhood home where his parents (Claire Foy and Jamie Bell), appear to be living, just as they were on the day they died, 30 years before.

Cast: Andrew Scott, Paul Mescal, Jamie Bell, and Claire Foy

snippet.title: Paul Mescal & Andrew Scott Argue Over The Internet's Biggest Debates | Agree to Disagree
snippet.description:
We pitted the incredibly charming Paul Mescal and Andrew Scott against each other to settle some age-old debates in this hilarious episode of Agree to Disagree. The pair enthusiastically discuss whether bowling is embarrassing, what the BEST form of potato is, and share their very strong opinions on the immediate banning of karaoke and personalised number plates. 

All of Us Strangers is in UK & Irish cinemas now. 

00:00 - 00:41 - Intro
00:41 - 01:36 - Being good at bowling is really embarrassing 
01:36 - 02:44 - I would rather live without music than movies 
02:45 - 04:46 - Someone running up stairs on all fours would give me the ick
04:47 - 05:42 - People with personalised number plates should be banned 
05:43 - 07:00 - I would rather fight 100 duck-sized horses than one horse sized-duck
07:00 - 07:49 - Ballads should be banned from karaoke 
07:50 - 09:08 - Saying bless you after sneezing is a waste of time
09:09 - 10:18 - Roast is the best form of potato 
10:18 - 11:06 - You should only wear a band t shirt if you know all of their songs
11:06 - 11:39 - I've got a better dad joke than the person opposite me 
11:39 - 12:25  There is nothing romantic about two people sharing a shower
12:26 - 13:14 The person opposite me is a joy to work with

localized.title: Paul Mescal & Andrew Scott Argue Over The Internet's Biggest Debates | Agree to Disagree
localized.description:
We pitted the incredibly charming Paul Mescal and Andrew Scott against each other to settle some age-old debates in this hilarious episode of Agree to Disagree. The pair enthusiastically discuss whether bowling is embarrassing, what the BEST form of potato is, and share their very strong opinions on the immediate banning of karaoke and personalised number plates. 

All of Us Strangers is in UK & Irish cinemas now. 

00:00 - 00:41 - Intro
00:41 - 01:36 - Being good at bowling is really embarrassing 
01:36 - 02:44 - I would rather live without music than movies 
02:45 - 04:46 - Someone running up stairs on all fours would give me the ick
04:47 - 05:42 - People with personalised number plates should be banned 
05:43 - 07:00 - I would rather fight 100 duck-sized horses than one horse sized-duck
07:00 - 07:49 - Ballads should be banned from karaoke 
07:50 - 09:08 - Saying bless you after sneezing is a waste of time
09:09 - 10:18 - Roast is the best form of potato 
10:18 - 11:06 - You should only wear a band t shirt if you know all of their songs
11:06 - 11:39 - I've got a better dad joke than the person opposite me 
11:39 - 12:25  There is nothing romantic about two people sharing a shower
12:26 - 13:14 The person opposite me is a joy to work with

But Hunt Game Show isn't just about finding love; it's about personal growth, self-discovery, and the magic of human connection. We believe that true love can be found in the most unexpected places, and our show aims to prove just that.

So, if you're ready to witness the thrilling pursuit of love, to witness strangers take a leap of faith and discover their soulmates, then Hunt Game Show is the channel for you. Get ready for a rollercoaster of emotions, laughter, tears, and, of course, love. Tune in, cheer on your favorite contestants, and let Hunt Game Show remind you that love truly knows no boundaries.

snippet.title: Labour have "a year" to prove themselves | Andrew Marr | The New Statesman
snippet.description:
Keir Starmer and his new government must show the public they can deliver.

Subscribe on YouTube: https://www.youtube.com/channel/UC2DHAQOeEg-Z-4trARDXHRA?sub_confirmation=1

Labour have inherited broken public services, a sputtering economy and a skeptical electorate. They have pledged to move fast and indeed Keir Starmer's early moves indicate a different type of government. But they will need to provide tangible improvements in order to carry public opinion with them. 

Andrew Marr joins Hannah Barnes and Freddie Hayward on the New Statesman podcast to discuss how Starmer is already pulling important levers of power - including harnessing the local authority of metro mayors and the devolved nations - to make early progress in his "decade of national renewal".

They also discuss the election in France which saw progressive parties see off Marine Le Pen's right-wing National Rally - but will result in thorny coalition talks. How will this impact the UK?

Read more: Why Labour is dropping "Levelling Up"
https://www.newstatesman.com/politics/uk-politics/2024/07/why-labour-is-dropping-levelling-up

--

Andrew Marr is Political Editor for the New Statesman, and is one of the UK's most senior political journalists. He spent over 20 years at the BBC where he was Political Editor and hosted the wildly successful Andrew Marr show. He is now based in Westminster where he brings his deep experience of political reporting to his analysis of the most important events in UK politics. He also hosts Tonight with Andrew Marr on LBC Radio.

Watch more videos from Andrew Marr in this playlist: https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLSfumUEfFlcIG6GaFtC82AQ1tmT-9JGhl
--

On our YouTube channel you’ll find insight on the top news and global current affairs stories, as well as insightful interviews with politicians, advisers and leading political thinkers, to help you understand the political and economic forces shaping the world.

With regular contributions from our writers including Political Editor Andrew Marr and Hannah Barnes - host of the New Statesman podcast - we’ll help you understand the world of politics and global affairs from Westminster to Washington and beyond.

snippet.title: Jacob Rees-Mogg on why he lost his seat & the need for 'PROPER conservatism' | SpectatorTV
snippet.description:

The team also answer a range of audience questions, including: how will the Conservatives win voters back? Is Nigel Farage here to stay?

04:26 – Kate Andrews on Labour's economic outlook

19:16 – "Should the party move towards the right and embrace Reform?"

snippet.title: Get your Top Gadgets without Breaking the BANK  | #Aimteks #bank #savingmoney

Gadget Guru Hacks: Score Top-Tech Without Breaking the Bank

🎉 Welcome to "Gadget Guru Hacks," your go-to source for snagging the best tech without draining your wallet! 🚀

🔔 **Hit that subscribe button and ring the bell** so you never miss out on the latest tech hacks and deals! 🔔

---

In This Video:

Hey tech fam! Join me as I unveil the secrets to scoring top-tech gadgets without maxing out your credit card. From last year's flagship models to certified pre-owned deals, student and senior discounts, mastering sales, and exploring online marketplaces, I’ve got all the tips you need to stay tech-savvy on a budget. 

---

**Key Topics Covered:**

1. **Last Year's Flagship Models**: Discover how last year's flagship phones and laptops offer amazing value for a fraction of the cost. Websites like TechRadar and Wirecutter make finding these hidden gems a breeze!

2. **Certified Pre-Owned (CPO)**: Learn about Certified Pre-Owned gadgets that are inspected, refurbished, and come with warranties. Check out Amazon Renewed, Apple Certified Refurbished, and Best Buy Geek Squad Certified Refurbished for fantastic deals.

3. **Student & Senior Discounts**: Students and seniors, rejoice! Find out how to unlock exclusive discounts on your favorite tech brands like Apple and Dell.

4. **Sales & Clearance Events**: Black Friday, Cyber Monday, and seasonal sales are your best friends. Subscribe to tech blogs for sale alerts and stay ahead of the game.


5. Online Marketplaces**: Dive into online marketplaces like Swappa for amazing deals, but always prioritize caution and check seller ratings.

6. **Phone Carrier Upgrade Deals**: Phone carriers often offer refurbished phones at a discount when you sign up for a new plan. Compare plans and upgrade deals to find the best offer.

---

snippet.title: DJI Mini 4 Pro Flight Test in Vietnam
snippet.description:
The DJI Mini 4 Pro is a highly capable drone, and performing a flight test is a great way to familiarize yourself with its features. Here's a step-by-step guide to conducting a comprehensive flight test:

In this Video I am recording at some of my favorite locations in Danang Vietnam. I will take you through a low flight test and a distance test. 

If you want to see my full photography portfolio please check out the official website. www.batteristafoto.com

A little Drone technical review for you. 
### Pre-Flight Preparations
1. **Charge Batteries**: Ensure both the drone's and the controller's batteries are fully charged.
2. **Update Firmware**: Check for and install any firmware updates for the drone and controller.
3. **Check Weather Conditions**: Fly in calm weather conditions. Avoid strong winds, rain, or extreme temperatures.
4. **Inspect the Drone**: Verify that propellers are securely attached and undamaged. Check for any physical damage to the drone.
5. **Choose a Safe Location**: Select an open area free of obstacles, people, and no-fly zones.

### Initial Setup
1. **Power On**: Turn on the drone and the controller.
2. **Connect to the App**: Open the DJI Fly app on your smartphone and connect to the drone.
3. **Calibrate the Compass**: Follow the on-screen instructions to calibrate the compass.
4. **GPS Signal**: Wait for the drone to acquire a strong GPS signal.

### Basic Flight Test
1. **Takeoff**: Use the automated takeoff function or manually take off by pushing the control sticks.
2. **Hover**: Let the drone hover at a low altitude to ensure stability and proper functioning.
3. **Movement**: Test basic movements – forward, backward, left, right, up, and down.
4. **Yaw Control**: Rotate the drone clockwise and counterclockwise to test yaw control.
5. **Return to Home (RTH)**: Test the RTH function to ensure the drone returns to the takeoff point correctly.

### Advanced Maneuvers
1. **Speed Modes**: Test different speed modes (Cine, Normal, and Sport) to see how the drone handles in each mode.
2. **Obstacle Avoidance**: Fly the drone towards obstacles to test the obstacle avoidance sensors (if applicable).
3. **Automated Flight Modes**: Try out intelligent flight modes like QuickShots, ActiveTrack, and Waypoints.

### Camera and Gimbal Test
1. **Camera Settings**: Experiment with different camera settings (resolution, frame rate, etc.).
2. **Gimbal Control**: Test the gimbal by adjusting its angle and ensuring smooth operation.
3. **Photo and Video Quality**: Capture photos and videos to evaluate the image quality and stability.

### Post-Flight
1. **Landing**: Use the automated landing function or manually land the drone.
2. **Review Footage**: Check the captured footage and photos for quality and any issues.
3. **Inspect the Drone**: After landing, inspect the drone for any damage or wear.

By following these steps, you'll be able to thoroughly test the DJI Mini 4 Pro's capabilities and ensure it performs optimally for your specific needs.

snippet.title: DJI MINI 4 PRO SPOTLIGHT TEST! Vietnam - Almost crashes!! #djiglobal #djimini4pro
snippet.description:
Hi friends! In this video I am showcasing my new drone the DJI Mini 4 Pro. 
Talk about the options i have for the various modes and  performance / flight and video. 

To see my full photography portfolio please drop by the official website
www.batteristafoto.com

About Modes - DJI Mini 4 Pro 
The "spotlight mode" on the DJI Mini 4 Pro refers to a feature where the drone camera locks onto a subject and keeps it in the frame while the drone maneuvers around it. This is particularly useful for capturing dynamic shots where the subject is moving or when you want to focus on a specific object or person.

Here's how to use Spotlight Mode on your DJI Mini 4 Pro:

1. **Power on and Connect**:
   - Power on the drone and the remote controller.
   - Ensure your smartphone or tablet is connected to the controller and launch the DJI Fly app.

2. **Select Intelligent Flight Modes**:
   - After taking off, tap the Intelligent Flight Modes icon on the left side of the screen within the DJI Fly app.

3. **Activate Spotlight Mode**:
   - Select “Spotlight” from the list of available flight modes.

4. **Select Your Subject**:
   - You can either tap on the subject on your screen or draw a box around it to select it.
   - The drone will lock onto the subject and keep it in the frame.

5. **Control the Drone**:
   - While the drone is in Spotlight Mode, you can manually control its flight direction and altitude using the control sticks. The camera will continue to track and keep the subject in the frame automatically.

6. **Adjust Settings**:
   - You can adjust various camera settings to ensure the best shot, such as exposure, resolution, and frame rate.

7. **End Spotlight Mode**:
   - To exit Spotlight Mode, simply tap the mode icon again and select another flight mode or manually fly the drone as usual.

Spotlight Mode is a great tool for both beginners and experienced pilots to capture professional-looking footage with ease.

snippet.description:
The Silent Screams of Bloxburg | Roblox Movie

In the town of Bloxburg, the mayor's friends and family get an unexpected Halloween party invitation. Excited and unsuspecting, they gather for a night of fun. However, the festivities take a dark turn when mysterious murders start happening. Panic spreads as the once-friendly gathering becomes a real-life mystery. Time is running out, and the residents of Bloxburg must unmask the murderer before it's too late. 

A whodunit

Hello everyone! Thank you so much for tuning in. This Roblox Movie took countless hours of work; about a month in total! I hope you all enjoy the movie and I had a really fun time making it. Please consider subscribing if you enjoyed it!

snippet.title: Mermaid Twins for 24 Hour Challenge! Winner Opens New Surprise Mystery Gift From Game Master!
snippet.description:
Rebecca Zamolo spent 24 hours training to be a mermaid in real life! 

Recently Rebecca Zamolo recreated Christmas in summer to open surprise mystery gift from the game master. That was right before Matt and Rebecca tried pranking Maddie with her celebrity crush in a boys vs girls prank war were the best prank wins.  But first the game master network had to decide if the gm was good or evil in the game master test.  Now Rebecca and Maddie are getting ready for a 24 hour challenge of becoming a mermaid.  After they have. awkward situations they are greeted brainer the mermaid trainer which looks like Maddie's crush but in a secret disguise.  Matt turns into Elsa and starts working in disguise as a red hood spy postmates driver.  His first delivery is 20 frozen popsicles to a park for a secret meeting.  Rebecca and Maddie compete in challenges to see who will open the next mystery gift.  Mr X turns out to be the rhs spy and jumps in the car for another date.  Will Matt get information or will this turn into another bad idea.  He remembers 15 ways to get out of a first date and tries them.  Rebecca wins the race and the final test is to see who can find the most buried treasure.  Who do you think will win?  Now that they aren't little mermaid in real life any more do you think the next gift will give them a better clue? Thanks for watching my funny entertainment mystery vlog videos in 2020!

snippet.title: CATNAP: ABANDONED AT BIRTH! Poppy Playtime Animation
snippet.description:
🤭POPPY PLAYTIME🤫 -  https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=WHGC_HRG-0Q&list=PLOXLcG81QFibVBrgaxDfb34W1OLdsN7Hq

Mama Catnap is furious and armed against Catnap, she is sure that he is responsible for the loss of baby Catnap, fortunately Player arrives in time to calm things down, will they manage to solve the mystery?

00:00 - CATNAP: ABANDONED AT BIRTH! 
06:07 - CATNAP HAS KITTENS!
11:09 - CATNAP Has Only 24 HOURS to LIVE!? 

Original Animation Hornstromp - @HornstrompFNF3D

About Poppy Playtime

Poppy Playtime is a first-person survival horror where the player plays as a former employee of Playtime Co. who returns to the abandoned toy factory of said company after receiving a letter from the staff who were thought to have disappeared 10 years ago. The player discovers that the factory is filled with toys who are alive and malicious towards them, and starts looking for a way to escape the premises. Various VHS tapes can be found throughout the factory, each one giving a more in-depth explanation of the story. 

The game utilizes multiple puzzles throughout, which the player must solve in order to progress further, with some requiring a gadget named the GrabPack, a backpack that can be equipped with two extendable hands which can be used to pull and reach objects from a far distance, conduct electricity, and access certain doors; in Chapter 2, it can also be used to swing across gaps and, with a green hand obtained during gameplay, transfer electricity between sources.

Plot
Chapter 1 – A Tight Squeeze
The player receives a package that contains a VHS tape, which shows a commercial for the titular doll Poppy Playtime and tours of the factory before abruptly cutting to spliced-in footage of graffiti of a poppy, and a letter from the missing staff, requesting them to "find the flower". They then enter the abandoned toy factory and, after solving the code to a security door, acquire the GrabPack, which they use to unlock the door to the lobby. After entering the lobby, the player is introduced to Huggy Wuggy, who is on display in the center of the room. While trying to unlock one door in the lobby, the power suddenly cuts, forcing them to restore power in the power room.

After heading back to the lobby, they discover that Huggy has disappeared from his display. The player then restores power to a control panel in order to control an overhead crane and retrieve the right hand of the GrabPack, which they use to unlock a hatch to a conveyor belt that leads to the "Make-a-Friend" section of the factory, where they restore power to the machinery and manufacture a toy. They then place the toy in a scanner and open a door to a hallway which, after the player enters, Huggy suddenly appears from and chases the player through the vents. After reaching a dead-end, the player pulls down a box and breaks part of the conveyor belt, causing Huggy to fall to the bottom of the factory. They then head to the aforementioned graffiti and open a door to a hallway, leading to a room where they find Poppy in a case which the player opens, freeing Poppy.

Chapter 2 – Fly in a Web
After freeing Poppy from her case, the player explores the back halls of the factory, eventually finding the office of Elliot Ludwig, Playtime's founder. After entering the vents in the office, they encounter Poppy, who thanks them for freeing her and offers to help them escape the factory by giving them a code to activate the factory's train. However, she is grabbed and pulled deeper into the factory. As they approach the Game Station where the train is located, the player encounters Mommy Long Legs, who holds Poppy hostage and takes the red hand from the player's GrabPack. She challenges the player to win the three games in the Game Station, and in return will give the player the code for the train, threatening to kill them if they disobey the rules. Making their way through the factory, the player crafts the green hand for the GrabPack and then proceeds through the three games.

The player is able to obtain two parts of the code before escaping during the third game, fleeing into the tunnels beneath the factory. An enraged Mommy accuses them of cheating and pursues them through the tunnels and back up into the factory until she becomes caught in the teeth of an industrial grinder, killing her. A needle-fingered hand rises to take her broken body away. The player finds Poppy trapped in a spider web with the third part of the code. After freeing her, the player boards the train to escape. However, Poppy diverts the train, saying that she could not let the player leave yet due to the events that had occurred inside the factory, claiming that she knows the player can handle whatever comes next. The train runs out of control and derails near a sign pointing to "Playcare".

#PoppyPlaytime #PoppyPlaytimeChapter3 #HuggyWuggy

🤭POPPY PLAYTIME🤫 -  https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=WHGC_HRG-0Q&list=PLOXLcG81QFibVBrgaxDfb34W1OLdsN7Hq

Player has the opportunity to make some quick and easy money! Just keep an eye on the smiling critters while their mothers drop them off at the playground, something tells me it won't be so easy anymore..... xd

00:00 - SMILING CRITTERS, But Everyone's a BABY?!
05:45 - DOGDAY HAS PUPPIES! 
11:24 - CATNAP´S MEAN TWIN SISTER

Original Animation Hornstromp - @HornstrompFNF3D

About Poppy Playtime

Poppy Playtime is a first-person survival horror where the player plays as a former employee of Playtime Co. who returns to the abandoned toy factory of said company after receiving a letter from the staff who were thought to have disappeared 10 years ago. The player discovers that the factory is filled with toys who are alive and malicious towards them, and starts looking for a way to escape the premises. Various VHS tapes can be found throughout the factory, each one giving a more in-depth explanation of the story. 

The game utilizes multiple puzzles throughout, which the player must solve in order to progress further, with some requiring a gadget named the GrabPack, a backpack that can be equipped with two extendable hands which can be used to pull and reach objects from a far distance, conduct electricity, and access certain doors; in Chapter 2, it can also be used to swing across gaps and, with a green hand obtained during gameplay, transfer electricity between sources.

Plot
Chapter 1 – A Tight Squeeze
The player receives a package that contains a VHS tape, which shows a commercial for the titular doll Poppy Playtime and tours of the factory before abruptly cutting to spliced-in footage of graffiti of a poppy, and a letter from the missing staff, requesting them to "find the flower". They then enter the abandoned toy factory and, after solving the code to a security door, acquire the GrabPack, which they use to unlock the door to the lobby. After entering the lobby, the player is introduced to Huggy Wuggy, who is on display in the center of the room. While trying to unlock one door in the lobby, the power suddenly cuts, forcing them to restore power in the power room.

After heading back to the lobby, they discover that Huggy has disappeared from his display. The player then restores power to a control panel in order to control an overhead crane and retrieve the right hand of the GrabPack, which they use to unlock a hatch to a conveyor belt that leads to the "Make-a-Friend" section of the factory, where they restore power to the machinery and manufacture a toy. They then place the toy in a scanner and open a door to a hallway which, after the player enters, Huggy suddenly appears from and chases the player through the vents. After reaching a dead-end, the player pulls down a box and breaks part of the conveyor belt, causing Huggy to fall to the bottom of the factory. They then head to the aforementioned graffiti and open a door to a hallway, leading to a room where they find Poppy in a case which the player opens, freeing Poppy.

Chapter 2 – Fly in a Web
After freeing Poppy from her case, the player explores the back halls of the factory, eventually finding the office of Elliot Ludwig, Playtime's founder. After entering the vents in the office, they encounter Poppy, who thanks them for freeing her and offers to help them escape the factory by giving them a code to activate the factory's train. However, she is grabbed and pulled deeper into the factory. As they approach the Game Station where the train is located, the player encounters Mommy Long Legs, who holds Poppy hostage and takes the red hand from the player's GrabPack. She challenges the player to win the three games in the Game Station, and in return will give the player the code for the train, threatening to kill them if they disobey the rules. Making their way through the factory, the player crafts the green hand for the GrabPack and then proceeds through the three games.

The player is able to obtain two parts of the code before escaping during the third game, fleeing into the tunnels beneath the factory. An enraged Mommy accuses them of cheating and pursues them through the tunnels and back up into the factory until she becomes caught in the teeth of an industrial grinder, killing her. A needle-fingered hand rises to take her broken body away. The player finds Poppy trapped in a spider web with the third part of the code. After freeing her, the player boards the train to escape. However, Poppy diverts the train, saying that she could not let the player leave yet due to the events that had occurred inside the factory, claiming that she knows the player can handle whatever comes next. The train runs out of control and derails near a sign pointing to "Playcare".

snippet.title: KAUFMO ABSTRACTED NEED FRIENDS?! The Amazing Digital Circus UNOFICIAL Animation
snippet.description:
This is an unofficial video. The Amazing Digital Circus and all characters are property of Glitch Productions and Gooseworx
🎪THE AMAZING DIGITAL CIRCUS ~ 👉 https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KkZTDoycFMo&list=PL9mygVI8GHtJYwLv2R3ufhJzHDMzpoGPu

The usually terrifying abstracted kaufmo has given way to an unusual appearance today, he is infused with an attack of melancholy instead of irrational rage, and he cries for company to play and talk to someone, will someone dare to be his friend?

00:00 - KAUFMO ABSTRACTED NEED FRIENDS?!
03:33 - KINGER GET ABSTRACTED! 
06:24 - GANGLE GET ABSTRACTED! 
08:49 - CAINE GET ABSTRACTED! 
11:14 - JAX SAD STORY ORIGIN?!

Don't forget to SMASH the LIKE button and suscribe ❤️👍

🎨Original Animation Hornstromp -  @Hornstrompgames   👨‍🎨

Original The Amazing Digital Circus:
https://youtu.be/HwAPLk_sQ3w?si=zkhW9zfcykUXWAky

A young woman becomes trapped in a circus-themed computer game after donning a VR headset. She meets a group of other trapped humans – Jax, Ragatha, Gangle, Kinger, and Zooble – and, unable to recall her original name, is renamed "Pomni" by the AI ringmaster, Caine. Pomni notices an exit door while touring the circus, but the others dismiss her as delusional. While the others participate in a quest to gather geometrical critters called "Gloinks", Pomni accompanies Ragatha and Jax to visit Kaufmo, another human searching for an exit, but find he has succumbed to isolation and "abstracted", becoming a mindless beast. Attempting to help Ragatha after Kaufmo causes them both to glitch out, Pomni stumbles upon the exit door and goes through it instead, finding a labyrinth of office spaces that lead her to an out-of-bounds area called "the Void". Caine returns Pomni to the circus, where he imprisons Kaufmo in a cellar with other abstracted humans, and repairs Pomni and Ragatha's glitching, before revealing the "exit" to be an unfinished extension he made for the circus. He then treats everyone to a feast of unsustaining digital food, which the others enjoy while Pomni is left traumatized by her situation.

The Amazing Digital Circus (also known as Digital Circus or TADC) is an Australian-American independent computer-animated web series created by Gooseworx and produced by Glitch Productions.

#theamazingdigitalcircus #digitalcircus #pomni #amazingdigitalcircus
